Replace the eagerly-constructed `cloudLinkManager` module singleton with an accessor pair mirroring `get/setWorkspaceManager`, and route every consumer through it. This is the keystone task â€” nothing else in the decomposition can land until the seam exists. SEAM (apps/server/src/services/core/auth/cloud-link.ts) â€” the file currently ends with `/** Process-wide cloud-link manager used by the /api/cloud/* routes and startup. */
export const cloudLinkManager = new CloudLinkManager();` (verified at the tail of the file, :369). Delete that export and replace it with exactly: `let instance: CloudLinkManager | undefined;

/**
 * Construct the process-wide cloud-link manager. Called once at the composition
 * root ({@link start} in `index.ts`): with no options in production (real
 * `fetch`, real defaults), or with an injected fake `fetchImpl` under
 * `DORKOS_TEST_RUNTIME`. Returns the constructed instance.
 */
export function initCloudLinkManager(options?: CloudLinkManagerOptions): CloudLinkManager {
  instance = new CloudLinkManager(options);
  return instance;
}

/**
 * The process-wide cloud-link manager used by the `/api/cloud/*` routes and
 * startup. Throws if read before {@link initCloudLinkManager} runs â€” a loud,
 * helpful failure instead of a silent `undefined` dereference.
 */
export function getCloudLinkManager(): CloudLinkManager {
  if (!instance) throw new Error('CloudLinkManager not initialized');
  return instance;
}`. The `CloudLinkManager` class and `CloudLinkManagerOptions` interface are UNCHANGED â€” the constructor already accepts `options: CloudLinkManagerOptions = {}` (:157) and defaults `fetchImpl` to `undefined`, which downstream `requestDeviceCode`/`pollForToken`/etc. resolve to `defaultFetch = globalThis.fetch` in cloud-link-client.ts (:86) when absent â€” so `initCloudLinkManager()` called with no options reproduces today's production behavior byte-for-byte. ROUTES (apps/server/src/routes/cloud.ts) â€” replace the value import at :14, `import { cloudLinkManager } from '../services/core/auth/cloud-link.js';`, with `import { getCloudLinkManager } from '../services/core/auth/cloud-link.js';`. Replace all four call sites, calling `getCloudLinkManager()` fresh at each site (do not cache it in a module-level const â€” the accessor's whole point is always resolving the live instance): `POST /link/start` (:22) `const result = await cloudLinkManager.startLink();` â†’ `const result = await getCloudLinkManager().startLink();`; `GET /link/status` (:34) `res.json(cloudLinkManager.getStatus());` â†’ `res.json(getCloudLinkManager().getStatus());`; `POST /unlink` (:40) `await cloudLinkManager.unlink();` â†’ `await getCloudLinkManager().unlink();`; `GET /status` (:50) `res.json(cloudLinkManager.getSummary());` â†’ `res.json(getCloudLinkManager().getSummary());`. The routes stay thin; the handlers only ever run post-boot, so the guard never trips in practice. BOOT/STOP + WIRING SLOT (apps/server/src/index.ts) â€” drop the value import at :26, `import { cloudLinkManager } from './services/core/auth/cloud-link.js';`, and add `import { initCloudLinkManager, getCloudLinkManager } from './services/core/auth/cloud-link.js';`. In the existing runtime-registration block inside `async function start()` (:169), the `if (env.DORKOS_TEST_RUNTIME) { â€¦ } else { â€¦ }` block at :440-469, add `initCloudLinkManager();` as the LAST statement in BOTH branches (both call it with no options â€” real fetch, real defaults â€” since the fake factory does not exist until task 2.1 replaces the `if` branch's call with the fake-injected version; this task must leave the manager always initialized regardless of which later task has landed). Then replace `cloudLinkManager.initOnStartup()` at :1430 with `getCloudLinkManager().initOnStartup()`, and `cloudLinkManager.stop()` at :1479 with `getCloudLinkManager().stop()`. Both calls already run inside `start()`/`stop()` after the registration block executes, so the accessor's guard never trips. ROUTE TEST MOCK (apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/cloud.test.ts) â€” the existing suite (:6-20) mocks the module as `vi.mock('../../services/core/auth/cloud-link.js', () => ({ cloudLinkManager: { startLink: vi.fn(), getStatus: vi.fn(), unlink: vi.fn(), getSummary: vi.fn() } }));` then `import { cloudLinkManager } from '../../services/core/auth/cloud-link.js'; const manager = vi.mocked(cloudLinkManager);`. Change the mock to export `getCloudLinkManager: () => mockManager` where `mockManager` is the same four-method object literal (hoist it above the `vi.mock` call or inline it per Vitest's mock-factory hoisting rules), and change the import/assignment to `import { getCloudLinkManager } from '../../services/core/auth/cloud-link.js'; const manager = vi.mocked(getCloudLinkManager());` (or equivalent â€” the goal is that `manager.startLink`/`getStatus`/`unlink`/`getSummary` remain the exact same mock fns the existing 8 `it(...)` cases already assert against, so no test-body changes are needed beyond the mock/import lines). SEAM CONSTRUCTION UNIT TESTS â€” add to `apps/server/src/services/core/auth/__tests__/cloud-link.test.ts` (extend the existing suite, which already imports `CloudLinkManager` directly and constructs fresh instances per test in nested `describe`/`beforeEach` blocks, :6,44-68) or a new sibling `cloud-link-seam.test.ts` â€” three cases per the spec's Testing Strategy: (a) `initCloudLinkManager()` with no options, then `getCloudLinkManager()` returns a `CloudLinkManager` instance; spy on `globalThis.fetch` (e.g. `vi.spyOn(globalThis, 'fetch').mockResolvedValue(...)`), drive `getCloudLinkManager().startLink()`, and assert the spy was called â€” proving the prod-default construction is behavior-preserving and never touches a fake. (b) `initCloudLinkManager({ fetchImpl: spy })` then `getCloudLinkManager().startLink()` calls `spy`, not `globalThis.fetch` â€” proving the seam is injectable. (c) Calling `getCloudLinkManager()` with no prior `initCloudLinkManager()` call in that test (reset module state first, e.g. `vi.resetModules()` + a fresh dynamic `await import('../cloud-link.js')`, since `instance` is module-level singleton state that otherwise leaks across test files/cases) throws exactly `'CloudLinkManager not initialized'`. Each test carries a one-line purpose comment. Acceptance: `cloud-link.ts` exports `initCloudLinkManager`/`getCloudLinkManager` and no longer exports `cloudLinkManager`; `routes/cloud.ts` and `index.ts` both resolve the manager only through the accessor; `cloud.test.ts`'s existing 8 cases pass unchanged against the new mock shape; the 3 new seam construction cases pass. Verify: pnpm --filter @dorkos/server typecheck && pnpm --filter @dorkos/server lint && pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/cloud.test.ts apps/server/src/services/core/auth/__tests__/cloud-link.test.ts. Cites: spec Â§Detailed Design 1 (exact accessor-pair code block), Â§Decisions resolved ("Seam shape â€” the accessor pair, not a mutable export. RESOLVED" â€” the `get/setWorkspaceManager` precedent chosen over the `configManager` mutable-export pattern, which is explicitly rejected as a foot-gun with no pre-init guard), Â§Code structure & file organization table, Â§Testing Strategy ("Seam construction unit â€” the keystone honesty proof"), Â§References (all cited line numbers). No dependencies â€” this is the keystone task: 2.1's fake wiring, 3.1's capture drive, and every later task assume `init/getCloudLinkManager` already exist.

Register the two docs stills as a single pinned-shard flow and add the drive that captures both in one linear pass. REGISTRY (apps/e2e/capture/shots.ts) â€” add to the "Desktop stills (docs-only; not on /features)" block (the block currently ends with the `marketplace-installed` entry, immediately before the `SHOTS_BY_ID` index construction): `{ id: 'accounts-pending', kind: 'still', frame: 'desktop', consumers: ['docs'] },
  { id: 'accounts-linked', kind: 'still', frame: 'desktop', consumers: ['docs'] },`. SHARD PIN â€” both stills come from ONE linear device flow (link â†’ pending â†’ auto-flip â†’ linked) and must ride the same shard, or a round-robin split (`partitionShots`) would put them on different stacks and break the flow. `SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS` currently reads `export const SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS: readonly string[] = ['multi-session', 'mobile-sessions', 'agent-discovery'];` â€” change it to `['multi-session', 'mobile-sessions', 'agent-discovery', 'accounts-pending', 'accounts-linked']`, following the same single-stack rationale the session-list shots already use (add a one-line comment explaining the accounts pair rides shard 0 because both stills come from one linear flow). UPDATE THE PIN ASSERTION (apps/e2e/capture/__tests__/shots.test.ts) â€” the existing `it('pins the session-list surfaces and agent-discovery', ...)` case asserts `expect(SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS).toEqual(['multi-session', 'mobile-sessions', 'agent-discovery']);` then `for (const id of SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS) expect(getShot(id)).toBeDefined();`. Update the `toEqual` array literal to match the new 5-element `SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS`; the `getShot(id)` loop passes unchanged once the registry entries above exist. THE DRIVE (apps/e2e/capture/surfaces-desktop.ts) â€” `attempt` and `isShotSkipped` are already imported from `./lib.js` at the top of this file (used by the existing `captureAgentDiscovery`), so no new import is needed for those two. Add, as a new function (selectors verified against `apps/client/src/layers/features/cloud-link/ui/CloudLinkPanel.tsx`): `/** Open Settings â†’ DorkOS account, link, and shoot the pending then linked states. */
async function shootCloudLink(page: Page, theme: Theme, rec: RunRecorder): Promise<void> {
  await page.goto(url('/agents?settings=account'));
  await page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'DorkOS account' }).waitFor({ timeout: WAIT_MS });
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Link this instance' }).click({ timeout: WAIT_MS });

  // Pending: the code + the "waiting" status render immediately (optimistic).
  await page
    .getByText('Waiting for you to approve', { exact: false })
    .waitFor({ timeout: WAIT_MS });
  await shoot(page, 'accounts-pending', theme, rec);

  // Linked: the fake auto-flips; the client's 2500ms status poll lands "Linked"
  // within a couple of ticks. Wait the money state â€” no arbitrary sleep.
  await page.getByText('Linked', { exact: true }).waitFor({ timeout: WAIT_MS });
  await page.getByText('Dork Labs', { exact: false }).waitFor({ timeout: WAIT_MS });
  await shoot(page, 'accounts-linked', theme, rec);
}` â€” `shoot`, `url`, `WAIT_MS` are already imported from `./lib.js`/`./config.js` at the top of the file (used by every existing `shoot*` function). INVOKE IT â€” place the call at the very END of `captureLightStills` (after the current last statement, the `shootWorkbench` call), so linking persists a token into the isolated capture config only after every earlier surface has already been shot (running last keeps that state from bleeding into any earlier surface): `if (!isShotSkipped('accounts-pending')) {
  await attempt('accounts (pendingâ†’linked)', () => shootCloudLink(page, theme, rec));
}` â€” this mirrors the `captureAgentDiscovery`/`isShotSkipped` guard pattern already used at surfaces-desktop.ts:513 (skip when a human override supplies it, or it belongs to another shard). CRITICAL SEQUENCING NOTE: the capture stack always runs with `DORKOS_TEST_RUNTIME=true` (apps/e2e/capture/boot.ts:42), so clicking "Link this instance" always calls `getCloudLinkManager().startLink()` on the server. Without task 2.1 landed first, that resolves to the real-fetch default from task 1.1 and would attempt a live `fetch` to `https://dorkos.ai` inside the sandbox (hanging or failing the drive) â€” so this task's drive is only exercisable once 2.1's fake wiring is live. NO CHANGES TO config.ts â€” per the spec's resolved correction, the pinned `user_code`/`accountLabel` live in the fake (server-side, task 2.1), not in `apps/e2e/capture/config.ts` (a different package the fake cannot import); the drive above waits on selectors, never on the exact code string, so no new pinned values are needed here. Acceptance: `accounts-pending` and `accounts-linked` are registered with `consumers: ['docs']`; both are in `SHARD_0_PINNED_SHOTS`; the `shots.test.ts` pin-equality assertion matches; `shootCloudLink` exists and is invoked exactly once, guarded, at the end of `captureLightStills`. Verify: pnpm --filter @dorkos/e2e typecheck && pnpm vitest run apps/e2e/capture/__tests__/shots.test.ts. Cites: spec Â§Detailed Design 5 (registry + shard pin + drive, exact code blocks), Â§Decisions resolved ("Determinism lives in the fake, not apps/e2e/capture/config.ts"), Â§Code structure & file organization table, Â§References (capture pipeline file:line citations). Depends on 2.1 (the drive is only meaningfully exercisable once the fake is wired â€” see the sequencing note above; the spec's own Implementation Phases explicitly orders Phase 3 after Phase 2).
